The class s_rails installs the necessary components for a Ruby on Rails application
environment.

Required variables:

  $rvm_default_ruby - The version string of the default ruby to be installed via RVM
    upon the server. (Note this is not required by s_rails, but by the s_ruby::rvm
    class that is included within.

Optional variables:

  $railsenv - If set, the apache directive "RailsEnv" will be set to the variable's
    value in /etc/httpd/conf.d/z-RailsEnv.conf.  If not set, "RailsEnv" will be set
    to "production".

